==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: corynebacterium
<hw>co`ry*ne`bac*ter"i*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(MIcrobiol.)</fld> <def>Any member of the genus
<gen>Corynebacterium</gen>, consisting of gram-positive usually
nonmotile irregularly rod-shaped bacteria, some of which are pathogenic
or parasitic in humans and domestic animals, such as
<spn>Corynebacterium diphtheriae</spn>, which causes
diphtheria.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coryphaenoid</ent>⟦br⟧
